the biggest highlights i remember:
mit
- iap, four week period in january to just do stuff, u can like take classes, do an internship, anything you want really. 
- more focused stem culture?
- big party culture if ur into that lol
- can take classes at harvard

stanford
- coterm program (get masters in like a year lol)
- startup culture
- more diverse people, like not jsut stem lol

boston vs bay area is def something to take into consideration, different weather, etc. i would rec visiting and just gauge the vibe, i honestly thought i would really wanna be in boston but after coming to stanfrod ive realzied im much more of a cali person, so its def up2u

if ur going in for stem (which ima assume since mit lol) lwk both are super good, tho i can really only speak for math and cs, if ur interested in like robotics mit should be better, for other fields i cant really speak, but if its anything cs you really cant go wrong in either place
stanford and mit are both phenomenal schools, imo it comes down to what u wanna get outta the college experience
